name: Dave Jackman
text: South Hall is pretty good. Hopefully all the painful construction will help the horrendous parking.

name: Martha Livingston
text: I attended a crafts show on a Sunday with approximately 80 vendors(?). There is a parking garage. Parking can cost $10. It was not crowded and the crafts were mainly Christmas themed due to the time of year. There was one concession inside that sold the usual snacks and drinks.

name: Cody Olivier
text: Great arena for a concert. Saw Fire From the Gods, Bad Wolves, Three Days Grace and Five Finger Death Punch! Great time. Concession prices are pretty high but what else is new there?

name: Blake Hargrove
text: Recently visited the South hall for a robotics competition. The event was awesome, and there were a couple of other things to do while we were there.

name: Ryan Cass
text: Excellent Event Center

name: Kim Massey
text: We had our Jehovah's Witnesses convention in the South Hall this year. I really liked the venue. Very easy to navigate. Convenient parking for disabled. Also, it was easy to get too coming from out of state. I really hope we will be able to use this facility in the future!

name: ANGEL'S COMICS
text: Awsome

name: Nancy Jones
text: Nice place to hold Convention of Jehovah's Witnesses in! Clean, cool, plenty of restrooms, great parking garage, polite people helping with traffic all 3 days! Would love to come again.

name: Deborah O'Neal
text: The craft show was missing a lot of vendors that I usually shop with. Hopefully that won't be the case next time.

name: Megan DeAngelis
text: Working here is so awesome. Come and see what we've got to offer!! You'll love it

name: Mark Toland
text: Attended a CASC show. Decent show. People were very nice. Hall was air conditioned and nice at 100 out side.

name: Melinda Botterbusch
text: Great convention center!

name: Josh Evans
text: Gorgeous

name: Matt Zawacki
text: Big space.

name: melissa Dunn
text: Loved all the crafts

name: Michelle Walker
text:
Went for volleyball regional tournament.
Great facility.  Handicap accessible.
Wonderful experience.

name: Toney Bartlett
text: Love seeing my brothes and sisters here

name: Harry Hall
text: Very organized and accommodating for trade shows

name: Kersta Le Sieur
text: Love

name: Joshua Hill
text: The South Hall space is just okay... It handles events well and the staff is friendly. Biggest thing to me is that it's dated and the restrooms are subpar.

name: Jeanmarie Caudle
text: Long walk, food was very expensive and not that good.

name: joan folsom
text: Clean, cool, & convenient!

name: Clarence Harris
text: Great volleyball tournament
